    • testCatInDirectory

      public void testCatInDirectory()
      Tests that cat works properly when users has cd into a directory. For example, if user cd's into dir1 then cat should handle filepaths relative to dir1. That is, if there's a file f1.txt in dir1, then cat f1.txt should produce the output of f1.txt. This is like RedirectionTests.testDirectoryShiftedRedirection().
